    "date": "2026-04-05",
    "title": "He Is Risen — The Resurrection of Jesus Christ",
    "scriptureReference": "Matthew 28:5-6",
    "scriptureText": "And the angel answered and said unto the women, Fear not ye: for I know that ye seek Jesus, which was crucified. He is not here: for he is risen, as he said. Come, see the place where the Lord lay.",
    "content": "In this season when believers around the world celebrate the resurrection of Christ, we hear the most revolutionary words ever spoken: He is not here — He is risen! An angel delivered this announcement to women who had come to anoint a dead body. Instead, they found an empty tomb, a rolled-away stone, and a message that would change the course of human history.\n\nThe resurrection of Jesus Christ is the central event of the Christian faith. Without it, the cross is a tragedy, the disciples are deluded, and our faith is empty. But because Jesus rose from the dead, everything He said is validated, everything He promised is guaranteed, and everything He accomplished is permanent. The resurrection is the divine stamp of approval on the entire gospel.\n\nNotice the angel's words: \"He is risen, as he said.\" Jesus had predicted His own resurrection multiple times during His ministry. He told His disciples that the Son of Man would be killed and on the third day would rise again. The resurrection was not an improvisation — it was the predetermined plan of God, announced in advance and fulfilled with absolute precision.\n\nThe empty tomb is the most scrutinized claim in human history. Skeptics have proposed every alternative explanation: the disciples stole the body, Jesus merely fainted, the women went to the wrong tomb. But none of these theories withstand examination. The Roman guard, the sealed stone, the grave clothes left behind, the post-resurrection appearances to over five hundred witnesses — the evidence is overwhelming.\n\nToday, whether you are celebrating Easter for the first time or the fiftieth, let the reality of the empty tomb fill you with unshakeable hope. The Jesus who conquered death is alive today. He is not a historical figure to be studied — He is a living Savior to be encountered. He is risen. He is here. And He invites you to experience the power of His resurrection in your own life.",
