    "date": "2026-04-06",
    "title": "The Power That Raised Him Lives in You",
    "scriptureReference": "Ephesians 1:19-20",
    "scriptureText": "And what is the exceeding greatness of his power to us-ward who believe, according to the working of his mighty power, Which he wrought in Christ, when he raised him from the dead, and set him at his own right hand in the heavenly places.",
    "content": "In this season when many believers celebrate the resurrection, Paul reveals a truth that transforms how we live: the same power that raised Jesus from the dead is available to those who believe. This is not a metaphor. This is not inspirational poetry. This is the literal, resurrection-grade power of God operating in the life of every believer.\n\nPaul uses four Greek words to describe this power: dunamis (raw power), energeia (working energy), kratos (dominion strength), and ischus (inherent might). He stacks these words on top of each other to communicate something language can barely contain: the power available to you is the same power that conquered death itself.\n\nConsider what that power accomplished. It took a dead body — three days in the grave, wrapped in burial cloths, sealed in a tomb — and raised it to immortal, glorified life. It reversed the irreversible. It conquered the unconquerable. It accomplished what no army, no technology, and no human effort could ever achieve. And that power lives in you.\n\nThis power is not dormant. It is not theoretical. It is \"to us-ward who believe\" — directed toward you, active in you, and available to you right now. Whatever you are facing — addiction, depression, broken relationships, financial crisis, spiritual dryness — the power that raised Jesus from the dead is more than sufficient to bring resurrection to your situation.\n\nToday, stop measuring your challenges by your own strength and start measuring them by resurrection power. The same energy that rolled the stone away from the tomb can roll away every obstacle in your life. You are not limited to human resources. You have access to the power that defeated death.",
