    "date": "2026-04-07",
    "title": "Risen with Christ — Seek Things Above",
    "scriptureReference": "Colossians 3:1-3",
    "scriptureText": "If ye then be risen with Christ, seek those things which are above, where Christ sitteth on the right hand of God. Set your affection on things above, not on things on the earth. For ye are dead, and your life is hid with Christ in God.",
    "content": "In this season when many believers celebrate resurrection, Paul connects the historical event of Christ's rising to the daily experience of every believer: if you have been raised with Christ, seek the things above. The resurrection is not just something that happened to Jesus two thousand years ago. It is something that has happened to you. You have been raised with Him.\n\nThe phrase \"if ye then be risen with Christ\" assumes it as fact for the believer. In God's eyes, when Christ rose, you rose with Him. Your spiritual resurrection is as real as His physical resurrection. You are no longer defined by the old life, the old identity, or the old limitations. You are a new creation, raised to walk in newness of life.\n\nPaul's instruction is practical: set your mind on things above, not on earthly things. This does not mean you ignore your responsibilities on earth. It means you evaluate everything through the lens of eternity. Your priorities, your ambitions, your use of time and resources — all of it should be shaped by the reality that you are a citizen of heaven living temporarily on earth.\n\nThe most stunning phrase in this passage is \"your life is hidden with Christ in God.\" This is the ultimate security. Your life is not exposed to the whims of the world — it is hidden, protected, enclosed within the person of Christ, who is Himself enclosed within God. To get to you, the enemy would have to get through God and then through Christ. That is impossible.\n\nToday, live as a risen person. You are not crawling out of the grave — you are seated with Christ in heavenly places. Your perspective, your identity, and your security have all been transformed by the resurrection. Set your mind on the things above, because that is where your true life resides.",
    "prayerPoints": [
      "Father, I am risen with Christ. I set my mind on things above, where Christ sits at Your right hand.",
      "Lord, help me to evaluate every priority, ambition, and decision through the lens of eternity. I am a citizen of heaven.",
      "Holy Spirit, remind me daily that my life is hidden with Christ in God. I am secure, protected, and beyond the enemy's reach.",
      "Father, I refuse to live as though I am still in the grave. I am raised, I am new, and I am seated with Christ.",
      "Lord, transform my perspective. Let the resurrection reshape how I see myself, my challenges, and my future."
    ],
