    "date": "2026-04-11",
    "title": "Resurrection Assurance — Because He Lives, You Will Live",
    "scriptureReference": "John 14:19",
    "scriptureText": "Yet a little while, and the world seeth me no more; but ye see me: because I live, ye shall live also.",
    "content": "In this season when many believers celebrate the power of the resurrection, Jesus' promise in John 14:19 shines with particular brilliance: because I live, you shall live also. The resurrection of Christ is not an isolated event. It is the guarantee of your own eternal life. His rising ensures your rising. His victory secures your victory.\n\nJesus spoke these words to His disciples on the night before His crucifixion. They were troubled, confused, and afraid. He was about to leave them through the most horrific death imaginable. But in the midst of their distress, He gave them the most reassuring promise they would ever hear: because I live, you shall live also. Your life is connected to Mine — and I am going to conquer death.\n\nThe world would no longer see Him after His ascension. But the disciples would see Him — not just physically in the post-resurrection appearances, but spiritually through the indwelling Holy Spirit. The risen Christ is not absent from His people. He is present in a way that is more intimate than physical proximity. He lives within every believer through the Spirit.\n\nThis promise extends beyond physical life. The \"life\" Jesus offers is zoe — the abundant, eternal, qualitatively different life of God Himself. This is not merely existence. It is life in its fullest, richest, most vibrant form — life that death cannot interrupt, circumstances cannot diminish, and time cannot erode.\n\nToday, you live because He lives. Your heartbeat is sustained by the same power that raised Jesus from the dead. Your future is secured by the same promise that emptied the tomb. And your present moment — whatever it holds — is filled with the presence of a living Savior who has promised that His life guarantees yours.",
