    "date": "2026-05-03",
    "title": "A Mother's Heart — The Foundation of Faith",
    "scriptureReference": "Proverbs 31:26-28",
    "scriptureText": "She openeth her mouth with wisdom; and in her tongue is the law of kindness. She looketh well to the ways of her household, and eateth not the bread of idleness. Her children arise up, and call her blessed; her husband also, and he praiseth her.",
    "content": "While celebration dates vary across nations, the honoring of mothers is a universal value that transcends every culture. The Bible places extraordinary significance on the role of mothers — and Proverbs 31 paints the portrait of a woman whose influence shapes families, communities, and generations.\n\nThe Proverbs 31 woman opens her mouth with wisdom. She does not speak carelessly or react impulsively. Her words are measured, intentional, and laced with kindness. This is not weakness — it is the strength of a woman who understands that her words have the power to build or to break. She chooses to build.\n\nShe looks well to the ways of her household. This phrase describes vigilance, stewardship, and proactive care. She is not merely maintaining a home — she is cultivating an environment where children thrive, where values are transmitted, and where faith is lived out in the daily rhythms of life. Her home is not perfect, but it is purposeful.\n\nThe reward of her faithfulness is beautiful: her children arise and call her blessed. This is not flattery — it is recognition. When children grow old enough to understand the sacrifices their mother made, the sleepless nights, the prayers whispered in secret, the meals prepared with love, the discipline administered with tears — they rise and call her blessed.\n\nToday, whether your mother is present or in heaven, living nearby or far away, whether your relationship with her is close or complicated — honor the gift of motherhood. And if you are a mother, know that your influence is incalculable. The seeds you plant in the hearts of your children will bear fruit for generations.",
