    "date": "2026-05-31",
    "title": "Restoring Families — Turning Hearts Together",
    "scriptureReference": "Malachi 4:6",
    "scriptureText": "And he shall turn the heart of the fathers to the children, and the heart of the children to their fathers, lest I come and smite the earth with a curse.",
    "content": "The very last verse of the Old Testament carries a prophetic promise about the restoration of family relationships. Before the coming of the Lord, hearts will be turned — fathers toward children, and children toward fathers. This is not merely a prediction — it is a divine priority. The healing of families is at the heart of God's agenda.\n\nThe fact that God closes the Old Testament with a word about family restoration reveals how central the family unit is to His purposes. Before He addresses nations, politics, economics, or culture, He addresses the home. When families are broken, everything downstream is affected — communities, churches, cities, and nations. But when families are healed, the blessing flows outward in every direction.\n\nThe phrase \"turn the heart\" implies that hearts have been turned away. Fathers have turned away from their children — through absence, neglect, addiction, workaholism, or emotional disconnection. Children have turned away from their parents — through rebellion, resentment, or the breakdown of communication. But God promises a turning — a restoration that only His Spirit can accomplish.\n\nThis turning of hearts is not a passive process. It requires intentionality, vulnerability, and often forgiveness. Fathers must choose to be present, engaged, and emotionally available. Children must choose to honor, forgive, and rebuild bridges that have been damaged. And both must invite God into the process, because only divine love can heal wounds that are generations deep.\n\nToday, wherever there is brokenness in your family — between parents and children, between siblings, between generations — know that God's heart is for restoration. He is in the business of turning hearts. And the promise of Malachi 4:6 is still active, still available, and still powerful enough to heal the deepest family wounds.",
