    "title": "The Promise of the Spirit — Power from on High",
    "scriptureReference": "Acts 1:8",
    "scriptureText": "But ye shall receive power, after that the Holy Ghost is come upon you: and ye shall be witnesses unto me both in Jerusalem, and in all Judaea, and in Samaria, and unto the uttermost part of the earth.",
    "content": "In this season of resurrection celebration, one of the final promises Jesus made before ascending to heaven was the gift of the Holy Spirit. He told His disciples not to leave Jerusalem until they had been endued with power from on high. The resurrection was the event. The Holy Spirit was the empowerment. Without the Spirit, the disciples would have had a story to tell but no power to tell it.\n\nThe word \"power\" is dunamis in Greek — the root of our word \"dynamite.\" This is not organizational power, political power, or intellectual power. It is explosive, supernatural, miracle-working power that comes exclusively from the Holy Spirit. Jesus did not say you will receive strategies, programs, or techniques. He said you will receive power.\n\nThe geography of Acts 1:8 is instructive: Jerusalem, Judaea, Samaria, and the uttermost part of the earth. The gospel moves in concentric circles — from the local to the regional to the cross-cultural to the global. This is the pattern of Spirit-empowered witness: start where you are, expand to your region, cross cultural boundaries, and ultimately reach the ends of the earth.\n\nThe disciples obeyed. They waited in the upper room. And on the Day of Pentecost, the Holy Spirit came with wind and fire, and the Church was born. Three thousand people were saved in a single day. The same disciples who had hidden behind locked doors after the crucifixion were now preaching boldly in the streets of Jerusalem. The difference was not education, strategy, or courage — it was the Holy Spirit.\n\nToday, the same power that fell at Pentecost is available to every believer. The Holy Spirit is not a doctrine to be debated — He is a Person to be received. And when He comes upon you, you become a witness with dunamis — explosive, unstoppable, world-changing power.",
